programme.title: Great Games: All-Star
programme.desc: Ichiro Suzuki makes history in 2007 by hitting the first ever inside-the-park home run during an All-Star Game. He was rewarded MVP for going 3-for-3 at the plate and collecting two RBIs in an American League victory, 5-4.

programme.title: Great Games: All-Star
programme.desc: The 2008 MLB All-Star Game at Yankee Stadium was marked as the longest All-Star Game in history. It ended after 4 hours and 50 minutes in the 15th inning on a walk-of sacrifice fly from Michael Young.

programme.title: Great Games
programme.desc: 10/7/52: Mickey Mantle's 6th inning home run and Billy Martin's game-saving catch help the New York Yankees win their 4th straight World Series, beating the Brooklyn Dodgers in 7 games.

programme.title: Great Games
programme.desc: 10/14/65: Sandy Koufax finishes a complete-game shutout in Game 7 of the 1965 World Series to bring home a championship. The Dodgers' 2-0 victory was capped in the top of the 4th inning when runs scored on a homer and an RBI single.

programme.title: Great Games
programme.desc: 10/15/70: After allowing three runs in the 1st inning, Mike Cuellar silenced the Reds over the next eight frames to pitch a complete game. The Orioles offense backed his start, scoring nine runs on 15 hits to take Game 5 and win the 1970 World Series.

programme.title: Great Games
programme.desc: 10/22/75: Tony Pérez started the Reds' comeback in Game 7, smashing a two-run home run over the Green Monster and onto Lansdowne Street. Jim Burtan scored Ken Griffey in the top of the 9th to break a 3-3 tie and give the Reds their third World Series win.

programme.desc: According to new evidence, the Woolly Mammoth went on roaming until about the time the Pyramids were built.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Mount Kenya: African Heart of Ice
programme.desc: Mount Kenya soars over 5km into the air. It is the second highest mountain in Africa. At its summit, temperatures fluctuate from over 30 degrees celsius to below freezing.
programme.sub-title: Mount Kenya: African Heart of Ice

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Ngorongoro: Born of Fire
programme.desc: Ngorongoro is thought to have formed about 2.5 million years ago from a large volcano, whose cone collapsed inward after a major eruption. This fertile land is full of wildlife, from cunning hyena and proud lions to vast herds of wildebeest and elephants.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Namibia: Sands of Time
programme.desc: Namibia is an arid, rough land. However, it has been inhabited for thousands of years, by people as well as animals, and shows no sign of losing popularity with either.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Sahara: Life on the Edge
programme.desc: Watch Africa's Cape Coast that goes from the frigid waters of Cape Point to the sub-tropic seas of Kwazulu-Natal./After, see Africa's Dark Heart in the Congo which is seething with innumerable species./Last,learn about the largest desert in the world.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Congo: the Untamed Heart
programme.desc: Known for centuries as Africa's Dark Heart, the Congo is a multi-layered, three-dimensional world, seething with innumerable species. By peeling back the layers, we discover how this vast rainforest works, and expose the hidden lives of its inhabitants.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Cape Coast: Where Worlds Colide
programme.desc: Watch Africa's Cape Coast that goes from the frigid waters of Cape Point to the sub-tropic seas of Kwazulu-Natal.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Ethiopia: Land of Extremes
programme.desc: Landlocked and surrounded by five countries, Ethiopia is one of east Africa's forgotten lands. Seemingly passive deserts in fact seethe with fire, and cloud-piercing peaks shield a secret Eden of canyons and cliff-tops teeming with life.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Virungas: Land of Ice and Fire
programme.desc: It's home to some of the world's most iconic animals  including the African great apes.
programme.sub-title: Virungas: Land of Ice and Fire

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Lake Turkana: Land of the Crocodile
programme.desc: The largest of Africa's Rift valley lakes, Lake Turkana is at the heart of one of the harshest landscapes on the planet. Despite its hostile environment, man and beast have both worked out a way to survive.
programme.sub-title: Lake Turkana: Land of the Crocodile

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Nile: An African Odyssey
programme.desc: The Nile is the longest river in the world. Ancient Egypt, one of the history's most powerful civilizations, depended hugely upon it. Each year, it flooded, replenishing the fields with fertile silt. This automatic irrigation fueled Egypt's economy.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Okavango: Water in the Desert
programme.desc: The Okavango Delta, a huge emerald oasis in the burning heart of the Kalahari desert, is fed by the Okavango River and this perpetual cycle of wet and dry is the lifeblood of this extraordinary natural Eden.

programme.title: Wildest Islands: Vancouver Island: Rivers of Life
programme.desc: Vancouver island is the largest island off the west coast of North America. Glaciers fuel the flow of some of Canada's tallest waterfalls, and an endless network of rivers and creeks provides the ideal habitat for the pacific salmon.

programme.title: Wildest Islands: Caribbean: The Wild Side of Paradise
programme.desc: The Caribbean is a tropical paradise. From just a few meters wide, to hundreds of kilometers across, each of the over 7,000 islands are different, and each has its own unique wildlife.
programme.sub-title: Caribbean: The Wild Side of Paradise

programme.title: Wildest Islands: Sri Lanka: Monsoon Island
programme.desc: Lying like a teardrop in the Indian Ocean, Sri Lanka is an island that defies convention. Poised just six degrees above the equator, it's less than 75,000 km sq in size. But it has enough wildlife to rival a continent.

programme.title: Wildest Islands: Falkland Islands: Penguin Paradise
programme.desc: The Falkland's bleak, battered, and windswept archipelago lies 460 km from the South American mainland. Rugged mountains and expansive pristine coastline are a unique home for wildlife  especially for one of the world's most iconic flightless birds.

programme.title: Wildest Islands: Japan: Islands of Extremes
programme.desc: Japan's 7,000 islands stretch for over 2,400 km, and cover an incredible range of climates. Winter in the central and northern islands can be savage, but summer in the sweltering southern islands couldn't be more different.

programme.title: Wildest Latin America: The Andes: World in the Clouds
programme.desc: The longest chain of mountains in the world, the Andes run the length of western South America and dictate the climate for the whole continent. They include some of the highest peaks outside the Himalayas.
programme.sub-title: The Andes: World in the Clouds

programme.title: The Christmas Dragon
programme.desc: A group of orphans goes on a journey to restore the lost magic and save Christmas.

programme.title: 48 Christmas Wishes
programme.desc: After losing an entire town's letters to Santa, two junior Elves leave the North Pole and attempt to blend into small town life as they set out to retrieve every missing wish before Santa's sleigh departs on Christmas Eve.

programme.title: Christmas in Mississippi
programme.desc: Photographer Holly returns to Gulfport, Mississippi for Christmas. Their traditional holiday light show has been revived again since a hurricane struck five years earlier. She is shocked to learn the festival is run by her high school sweetheart, Mike.

programme.title: Christmas Harmony
programme.desc: Harmony's pop star boyfriend breaks up with her right before the holiday season, but when she returns to her hometown she discovers the heart and music that her life has been missing.

programme.title: A Gift Wrapped Christmas
programme.desc: Starring Meredith Hagner, Travis Milne, and Beverley Mitchell. Personal shopper Gwen's new client is a workaholic single father. When Gwen meets his 7-year-old son, she makes their lacking father-son relationship her Christmas mission.

programme.title: A Country Christmas Story
programme.desc: Musical icon and multiple Grammy Award winner Dolly Parton and Grammy Award nominated R&B singer and producer Brian McKnight star in this Lifetime Original Movie.

programme.title: A Bulldog For Christmas
programme.desc: Becky really hates Christmas. But when she is magically transformed into a cute bulldog, she has to learn the meaning of Christmas and get into the holiday spirit or she may never be changed back. An entertaining Christmas film for the whole family.

programme.title: The Christmas Lodge
programme.desc: During a weekend trip to the mountains, Mary finds herself at the now run-down lodge where she spent the holidays with her family growing up. She becomes determined to restore the building to its former glory

programme.title: The Christmas Switch
programme.desc: Through Eddie's wit and guile, he gives Sam that last night and finally finds the real meaning of Christmas the gambler's way.

programme.title: You Can’t Fight Christmas
programme.desc: Interior designer Leslie Major loves all things Christmas. When she meets handsome Edmund James, she quickly learns he thinks the festivities are frivolous and superficial.

programme.title: Grumpy Cat's Worst Christmas Ever
programme.desc: Grumpy Cat is an Internet meme sensation with over 6 million Facebook friends, who has graced the cover of New York Magazine, is the spokescat for Friskies, appeared on American Idol and the MTV Movie Awards.

programme.title: Peeples
programme.desc: Sparks - and laughs - fly when Wade Walker (Craig Robinson) crashes the Peeples' annual family reunion in the Hamptons to ask for their daughter's (Kerry Washington) hand in marriage.

programme.title: Relative Values
programme.desc: When a star and Hollywood Diva Miranda Frayle brek up, a playboy prince with a stiff upper lip sweeps her off her feet and boldly takes her home to meet his high class society minded mother.

programme.title: Love Potion #9
programme.desc: Paul, a geek biochemist with no luck at all with women, is persuaded by his friends to visit a gypsy. She gives him "Love Potion #9", an elixir which can potentially force anyone of the opposite sex to instantly fall in love with him.

programme.desc: One of the all-time great British black comedies! A man goes looking for his long lost dad – only to meet a voracious older woman who is, apparently, the sex bomb of Southend.

programme.desc: A harried workaholic, Michael Newman doesn't have time for his wife and children, not if he's to impress his ungrateful boss and earn a well-deserved promotion.

programme.title: Big Daddy

programme.desc: If you've always wanted to know what a baby thinks of the world around him, you finally have your chance. With Bruce Willis supplying the voice of Mikey's thoughts, this is one baby who says exactly what's on his mind. Rating: PG-13

programme.desc: Paul Blart is headed to Las Vegas to attend a Security Guard Expo with his teenage daughter Maya before she departs for college. While at the convention, he inadvertently discovers a heist – and it’s up to Blart to apprehend the criminals.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett
programme.desc: Richard investigates claims that the supposed mastermind behind the 9/11 terrorist attacks and leader of the Al Qaeda terrorist cell remained a CIA asset until his death.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett
programme.desc: Richard speaks with two investigative journalists and a natural health practitioner who maintain vaccines are neither safe nor effective.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett
programme.desc: Can radiation from electrical appliances, power lines, microwave ovens, and wireless technology such as cell phones, baby monitors, alter our DNA, and cause illnesses?
programme.sub-title: The Dangers of EMF (Electro Magnetic Frequencies)

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: Alien Abductions
programme.desc: Richard speaks with two alleged alien abductees about their claims they were taken aboard an alien space craft.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett
programme.desc: For centuries, farmers have been discovering strange, complex geometric patterns comprised of rings, circles and other intricate shapes in their fields.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett
programme.desc: Richard meets the owners of an abnormal humanoid skull allegedly discovered in Mexico in the 1930s and a researcher who has had the skull subjected to numerous tests including carbon-14 dating, and DNA in order to determine it’s origin.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: The Mystery of Oak Island
programme.desc: Richard investigates Canada's best-known mysteries, the Oak Island treasure. Also known as the money pit, the site has become one of the world's deepest and most costly archaeological digs.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: Energy Healing
programme.desc: Several energy healers claim they are able to produce spontaneous miraculous healing through a laying on of hands. Claims of similar such healing by a man in a remote village in Brazil, known as John of God are also examined.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: The Execution of MLK and The Framing of James Earl Ray
programme.desc: In this re-examination of the assassination of civil rights leader Martin Luther King, Richard meets several researchers who provide evidence that the convicted gunman, James Earl Ray was not the real triggerman.
programme.sub-title: The Execution of MLK and The Framing of James Earl Ray

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: The Birthers - Obama's Birth Certificate
programme.desc: Richard interviews several prominent 'Birthers' who present evidence that proves Barack Obama is not eligible to be President because he does not meet the qualifications of a natural born citizen.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: RFID Chips
programme.desc: Could implantable RFID chips or Radio-frequency identification tags currently in widespread use in retail industry be used to surreptitiously track and control people?

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: The Assassination of John Lennon
programme.desc: The Conspiracy Show travels to New York, LA and Toronto in order to investigate the murder of John Lennon. Several researchers posit that Lennon's supposed killer Mark David Chapman was either a patsy or a mind-controlled assassin.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: Did Jim Morrison Fake His Death?
programme.desc: Is it conceivable that the Doors legendary front man did not die in a bathtub in Paris of an apparent drug overdose?
programme.sub-title: Did Jim Morrison Fake His Death?

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: The Water Engine
programme.desc: Did the late Stanley Meyer figure out a way to run an internal combustion engine on pure water? And was he murdered because of the threat his invention posed to Big Oil?

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: The Murder of Marilyn Monroe
programme.desc: Did this pop icon and blond bombshell succumb to a drug overdose in 1962 as we've been led to believe or was she killed for 'knowing too much?

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: Is The Cure for Cancer Being Suppressed?
programme.desc: Richard investigates claims that the medical profession, drug companies, the food industry and government agencies are suppressing a cure for cancer.
programme.sub-title: Is The Cure for Cancer Being Suppressed?

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: The Bilderbergs
programme.desc: A glimpse backstage at the highly secretive annual gathering of the world's richest and most powerful movers and shakers.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: The Shroud of Turin
programme.desc: Is this famous piece of linen cloth the actual burial cloth of Jesus Christ or a clever Medieval hoax?

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: The Fake Arab Spring?
programme.desc: Who was really behind a series of revolts, protests, and uprisings that swept the Middle East starting in late 2010?

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: Ouija Boards?
programme.desc: Harmless board game or portal to the spirit world? Richard delves into the history and folklore of 'talking boards' with a collector of Ouija boards and a world renowned paranormal investigator.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: Global Warming, A Hoax?
programme.desc: Richard speaks with several journalists and researchers who argue the theory that human use of carbon-based fossil fuels will lead to catastrophic global warming.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: JFK
programme.desc: Richard meets with some prominent JFK assassination researchers to discuss the November 1963 murder of President John F. Kennedy.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: Pterodactyls
programme.desc: Richard speaks with several explorers and cryptozoologists who believe pterodactyls, flying dinosaurs thought to have become extinct some 60 million years ago, are alive and thriving in remote places such as Papua New Guinea.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: GMO - Genetically Modified Food
programme.desc: Richard investigates claims crop plants created for human or animal consumption using the latest molecular biology techniques are unsafe.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: Fluoride
programme.desc: The Conspiracy Show investigates the safety and efficacy of putting fluoride in our water supply. Dentists say that putting fluoride in the water supply prevents tooth decay, but some researchers claim it's a toxic substance that causes cancer.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: Area 51
programme.desc: What's going on inside Area 51, America's most carefully guarded secret? The mysterious military base located 30 minutes north west of Las Vegas has been rumored to be involved in back engineering advanced alien technology recovered from UFO crash sites.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: Remote Viewing
programme.desc: We meet several individuals who claim they have the ability to transcend time and space and identify people, objects, and locations hidden from their view.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: Freemasons
programme.desc: Are the Freemasons a harmless fraternity whose members busy themselves by raising money for children's hospitals or a satanic cult whose tentacles and enslave mankind?

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: The Depopulation Agenda
programme.desc: Richard interviews an investigative health reporter and a NY Times best-selling author about their claims that a powerful cabal is waging war on mankind through forced sterilization, vaccination and other means.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: Mokele Mbembe
programme.desc: Mokele Mbembe means able to stem the flow of rivers. The Pygmies there say they have encountered just such a creature and according to their descriptions, this behemoth is a dead ringer for an Apotosaurus.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: Bigfoot
programme.desc: Two prominent Bigfoot trackers and a cryptozoologist affirm the existence of this shy and elusive creature and relate several close encounters with Sasquatch.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: The O'Hare UFO Incident
programme.desc: Richard investigates a UFO sighting over Chicago's O'Hare airport that was witnessed by dozens of people, including an airline captain, his crew and several airport officials.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: The Philadelphia Experiment
programme.desc: Richard investigates a legendary naval military experiment said to have been carried out at the Philadelphia Naval Shipyard in October 1943.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: The Phoenix Lights
programme.desc: On March 13th, 1997, an extraordinary event occurred across the state of Arizona that has become the subject of great debate in the UFO community.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: Agenda 21
programme.desc: Is Agenda 21 simply a non-binding, voluntarily implemented action plan of the United Nations with regard to sustainable development?

programme.title: Myth Hunters
programme.desc: Mysterious and bizarre deaths happen when an amateur prospector searches for lost Aztec treasure. Is this the curse of Montezuma’s Treasure at work?

programme.title: Museum Secrets: Inside the Louvre
programme.desc: From murdered kings to stolen masterpieces, discover the secrets inside the Louvre.

programme.title: Museum Secrets: Inside the Bardo Museum, Tunisia
programme.desc: From the real lives of gladiators to the connection between Star Wars and Tunisia, discover the secrets inside the Bardo Museum.

programme.title: Museum Secrets: Inside the National Maritime Museum, London
programme.desc: From the musket shot that killed Admiral Nelson to an anti-piracy commando raid, discover the secrets inside the National Maritime Museum.
programme.sub-title: Inside the National Maritime Museum, London

programme.title: Museum Secrets: Inside the Uffizi Gallery, Florence
programme.desc: From a famous artist who vanished to a traitorous Nazi who saved the day, discover the secrets inside the Uffizi Gallery.

programme.title: Museum Secrets: Inside the Kunsthistorisches Museum, Vienna
programme.desc: From the alchemy of turning silver into gold to a dance craze that changed history, discover the secrets inside the Kunsthistorisches Museum.

programme.title: Museum Secrets: Inside the Natural History Museum, London
programme.desc: From Darwin’s original specimens to a lost workshop that inspired James Bond, discover the secrets of Britain’s Natural History Museum.
programme.sub-title: Inside the Natural History Museum, London

programme.title: Museum Secrets: Inside the National Museum of Anthropology, Mexico City
programme.desc: From ancient athletes who kick a severed head to a peasant dress that brings down an empire, discover the secrets inside the National Museum of Anthropology.
programme.sub-title: Inside the National Museum of Anthropology, Mexico City

programme.title: Museum Secrets: Inside the Pergamon and Neues Museums, Berlin
programme.desc: From Vikings who break unbreakable swords to curators who solve the world’s hardest jigsaw puzzle, discover the secrets inside the Pergamon and Neues Museums.
programme.sub-title: Inside the Pergamon and Neues Museums, Berlin

programme.title: Museum Secrets: Inside the National Archeological Museum of Athens
programme.desc: From a dodgy archeologist who discovers a golden mask to an ancient gadget that reveals the future, discover the secrets inside the National Archaeological Museum.
programme.sub-title: Inside the National Archeological Museum of Athens

programme.title: Museum Secrets: Inside The ROM, Toronto
programme.desc: From a medieval hand-grenade to an extremely rare dinosaur, discover the secrets inside the Royal Ontario Museum.

programme.title: Museum Secrets: Inside the State Historical Museum, Moscow
programme.desc: From the duel that killed a genius to Lenin’s Rolls-Royce, discover the secrets inside the State Historical Museum.
programme.sub-title: Inside the State Historical Museum, Moscow

programme.title: Museum Secrets: Inside the Metropolitan Museum, New York
programme.desc: From the mystery of a king’s madness to a silver chalice some think is the Holy Grail, discover the secrets inside the Metropolitan Museum.
programme.sub-title: Inside the Metropolitan Museum, New York

programme.title: Museum Secrets: Inside the Palacio Real, Madrid
programme.desc: From a clock that runs on witchcraft to a 21st Century king who outfoxes a fascist, discover the secrets inside the Palacio Real.

programme.title: Museum Secrets: Inside the Egyptian Museum
programme.desc: From the mystery of a Pharaoh’s gold to the strange practice of animal mummification, discover the secrets inside the Egyptian Museum.

programme.title: Museum Secrets: Inside the American Museum of Natural History, New York
programme.desc: From a dinosaur embryo that solves a murder mystery to a spacecraft catching a comet’s tail, discover the secrets inside the American Museum of Natural History.
programme.sub-title: Inside the American Museum of Natural History, New York

programme.title: Museum Secrets: Inside the Israel Museum, Jerusalem
programme.desc: From a scientist who recreates the crucifixion to an ancient amulet that proves Star Trek's Spock is Jewish, discover the secrets inside the Israel Museum.

programme.title: Museum Secrets: Inside the State Hermitage Museum
programme.desc: From ancient mummies who sport tattoos to re-examining who really killed Rasputin, discover the secrets inside the State Hermitage Museum.

programme.title: Museum Secrets: Inside the Smithsonian Institution, Washington DC
programme.desc: From the Zeros that bombed Pearl Harbor to the rocket that could take humans to Mars, discover the secrets inside the Smithsonian Institution.
programme.sub-title: Inside the Smithsonian Institution, Washington DC

programme.title: Museum Secrets: Inside the Imperial War Museum, London
programme.desc: From Churchill risking his life in the Blitz to 21st Century soldiers who become invisible, discover the secrets inside the Imperial War Museum.
programme.sub-title: Inside the Imperial War Museum, London

programme.title: Deadly Disasters: Landslides
programme.desc: Nothing can be done to prevent a landslide once it starts; they are among the most ferocious and devastating forces in nature.

programme.title: Deadly Disasters: Pandemics
programme.desc: With an ever more mobile world population, potentially growing in size to 11 billion people by the next century, public health experts agree that the possibility of a cataclysmic disease is more likely now than ever before.

programme.title: Deadly Disasters: Heatwaves
programme.desc: Temperatures in places like Saudi Arabia routinely exceed 40 degrees Celsius with very little effect on the population. However, when the same extreme heat struck the people of Russia in 2010, it killed an estimated 56,000 people.

programme.title: Deadly Disasters: Earthquakes
programme.desc: Many of our most densely populated cities are situated on the Earth’s most seismically active fault lines. Deadly, highly destructive, and impossible to predict, Earthquakes are truly one of Mother Nature’s most terrifying forces.

programme.title: Deadly Disasters: Volcanoes
programme.desc: Human history is littered with the stories of gigantic volcanic eruptions and the tragic fates of those who could not outrun the burning lava and poisonous gases. In our own times, volcanoes continue to cause large-scale destruction.

programme.title: Deadly Disasters: Blizzards
programme.desc: With ice, freezing temperatures, and ferocious winds — the Blizzard is one of Mother Nature’s most effective killing machines. They are typically associated with heavy snow, but may even occur when there is little or no snowfall.

programme.title: Naked Science: Making Mountains
programme.desc: The Rockies. Magnificent and awe-inspiring mysterious, the Rockies are one of the longest mountain ranges in the world. Naked Science investigates the geological processes that build these massive mountains.

programme.title: Naked Science: Snowball Earth
programme.desc: There is a theory that scientists once dismissed as absurd - that long ago the Earth became so cold every inch of it was entombed in ice.

programme.title: Naked Science: Anatomy Of A Hurricane
programme.desc: Hurricanes are one of the most destructive weather events to strike our planet and have the same power as a nuclear weapon.

programme.title: Naked Science: Super Flares - Could They Cause Mass Extinction?
programme.desc: Superflares are amongst the greatest events of the Universe. These magnetic explosions can release energy millions of times greater than atomic bombs. They produce streams of highly energetic particles which can be highly destructive to life.
programme.sub-title: Super Flares - Could They Cause Mass Extinction?

programme.title: Naked Science: The Great Flood
programme.desc: Almost every culture on Earth tells the story of an ancient flood – details vary but the basic plot is the same - An angry God wipes out an unrepentant population.

programme.title: Naked Science: How To Avert an Asteroid Impact
programme.desc: Throughout history, the earth has been bombarded from space. Asteroid impacts have caused mass extinctions – including the dinosaur wipe out.
programme.sub-title: How To Avert an Asteroid Impact

programme.title: Naked Science: Venus
programme.desc: Earth has an evil twin. Venus. It is shrouded in a lethal atmosphere of carbon dioxide and acid rain. The surface temperature is hot enough to melt lead and the pressure high enough to crush a nuclear submarine.

programme.title: Naked Science: The Big Bang - The First Three Seconds
programme.desc: 13.7 billion years ago there was absolutely nothing. No space, no time, and no matter. Naked Science follows the first three seconds of creation when a speck of light appeared from nothing and rapidly expanded into an enormous Universe.
programme.sub-title: The Big Bang - The First Three Seconds

programme.title: Naked Science: Magnetic Earth
programme.desc: The Earth hurtles through space protected by an invisible force field, known as a magnetosphere.

programme.title: Naked Science: Atmosphere
programme.desc: We breathe it every day, it protects us from solar radiation, controls our weather – it’s the atmosphere. Naked Science takes a trip from the earth to near space to understand how the earth’s atmosphere affects all life on the planet.

programme.title: Full Force Nature: Episode 105

programme.title: World's Greatest: Land Adventures
programme.desc: Most land adventures come with some risk - a chance to confront our deepest fears, resist the pull of the ordinary, and soar into the wild unknown.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Drives
programme.desc: A journey by road expands our horizons, allowing us to explore the depth and breadth of whole countries and continents, stopping whenever and wherever we chose.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Jungle Animals
programme.desc: Encounter gorillas and orangutans, killer tree-dwelling pythons, delightful monkeys, awe-inspiring tigers, and millions of land-dwelling red crabs in Australia, the islands of Southeast Asia, Africa, and the Amazon.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Volcanoes
programme.desc: There are few sights on earth as compelling as a volcanic eruption. Volcanoes have the potential to cause death and widespread destruction in a heartbeat, but they also give rise to new life and ecosystems.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Mega Cities
programme.desc: Mega Cities provide a bustling home to populations of over 10 million. Travel from the high-density living of Shanghai and Bangkok to the sprawling cities of Delhi and Mexico City, each the backdrop for dynamic cultures.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Lost Cities
programme.desc: Once powerful and populous centers of influence, these lost cities are providing clues to how our ancestors existed in the world and remind us that ancient civilizations were not so far removed from our own.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Forest Animals
programme.desc: Forest Animals gets up close with bears, koalas, moose, wolves, weaver ants, and Tasmanian Devils. This episode roves dark forests floors and soars above vast canopies of green in America, China, Laos, and Australia.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Mountains
programme.desc: The earth’s fragile crust has folded and faulted, and nowhere are these natural forces more evident than in the world’s great mountains. Explore the highest peaks of the world’s terrain - the rugged realm between heaven and earth.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Global Cities
programme.desc: Travel to the centers of wealth, power, industry, and innovation. From London to Tokyo, Hong Kong to New York, these are the cities that never sleep. The influence held in these economic hubs unites the global community.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Archipelagos
programme.desc: The romantic notion of island life has always attracted us. Explore the histories, cultures, and unique ways of life on the World’s Greatest Archipelagos - clusters of islands that share common bonds of geography, geology, and genealogy.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Extreme Animals
programme.desc: Extreme Animals features environments hostile to humans, but havens to many animals. Witness gorgeous glow-worms, high flying condors, parched thorny devils, emperor penguins, and polar bears in this journey through life on the edge.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Marine Animals
programme.desc: From the surprises of colorful reef characters to effervescent penguins, killer sharks, and regal whales, dive into the places where nature reveals itself in some of its most marvelous and bizarre forms.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Sacred Sites
programme.desc: Ancient in architecture and detailed in design, these man-made masterpieces stand as testaments to the strength of human faith. These sites endure as a timeless reminder of resilience, respect, and the need to reflect.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Ancient Cities
programme.desc: In Ancient Cities, we journey to these ancestors of influence such as Luang Prabang, Vienna, and Istanbul where religious and cultural centers have shaped the ways in which we view the world around us and continue to do so in modern times.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Capital Cities
programme.desc: With visionaries, politicians, and activists, these metropolises are defined as the official seats of government. Dublin, Washington, and Taipei share broad avenues, museums, and monuments, but are as varied as the countries they represent.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Treks
programme.desc: Every journey made by foot promises a grand adventure. From the highest mountains to the wildest jungle realms, treks venture down the road less travelled, allowing us to connect to nature, history, and culture, one step at a time.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Monuments & Landmarks
programme.desc: Many of the world’s most significant manmade wonders serve not as dwellings, but as powerful signposts. But more than giving us direction, they tell us a story - they characterize powerful forces, or commemorate power lost.

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory: Battle of Tobruk
programme.desc: German field marshal Erwin Rommel scores a major victory at the Libyan seaport of Tobruk.

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory: The Bombing of England (Fall 1940)
programme.desc: After invading France, Hitler is planning to cross the Channel. His only obstacle is the Royal Air Force. Throughout the summer of 1940, both sides lose an incredible number of daring flyers.

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory: The Battle of Norway (Early 1940)
programme.desc: Early in the war, the Germans decide they need to guarantee access to the Norwegian port of Narvik to ensure their supplies of Swedish iron ore. The British, however, send destroyers to up-end the German plan.

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory: Fall of Poland
programme.desc: German tanks roll into Poland in September 1939.

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory: Dunkirk (September 1, 1939)
programme.desc: To keep France free, 400,000 English soldiers have manned the battlefields. Germany's strength is too great and pushes the British to the coast town of Dunkirk.

programme.title: Rommel: The Soldier, The Son, and Hitler
programme.desc: Never a member of the Nazi party, Rommel detested blending politics and war. He would quickly discover that both were always in play under Hitler.

programme.title: VE Day - Forever in their Debt
programme.desc: Tells the stories of those who experienced the end of the war in all its many forms. It features a wide range of interviews from children who remember the street parties, to the servicemen who remember not having to buy a single drink that day.

programme.title: Hitler's Propaganda Machine: Building The Brand
programme.desc: Hitler’s fascination with propaganda was born in the trenches of the First World War. There he saw it emerge as a potent tool of psychological warfare - one that he would harness to build the Nazi movement. Witness Hitler's early propaganda tactics.

programme.title: Hitler's Propaganda Machine: Power and Persuasion
programme.desc: This episode explores Hitler's approach to propaganda in power; where persuasion was achieved through propaganda and terror, all in service of one goal: the creation of a state under one shared ideology. A new German power fueled by propaganda.

programme.title: Hitler's Propaganda Machine: Why We Fight
programme.desc: This episode explores the way Hitler used propaganda to justify his warmongering, reframing it as defense of Germany’s people and borders. It investigates the role propaganda played for both Hitler and the Allies to mobilize their countries for war.

programme.title: War Wrecks: The Untold Stories: The Tragic Sinking of Leopoldville
programme.desc: On the 24th of December 1944, 2 237 American soldiers of the 66th Infantry Division are aboard the Steamer Léopoldville.

programme.title: War Wrecks: The Untold Stories: Secret Bunkers of Omaha Beach
programme.desc: On June 6th 1944, Lieutenant-colonel Rudder’s Rangers company climbs the cliffs of the Pointe du Hoc in Normandy with the mission to destroy the German cannons.

programme.title: War Wrecks: The Untold Stories: The Last Flight of the B-17
programme.desc: Twenty-six metres beneath the waves at the foot of the majestic Calvi Citadel in Corsica lies an American plane from the Second World War.
programme.sub-title: The Last Flight of the B-17

programme.title: War Wrecks: The Untold Stories: The Lost Tanks of D-Day
programme.desc: In Normandy, June 6, 1944, a dozen Sherman tanks equipped with floats, the famous Duplex Drives (DD), leave their ship to swim to Omaha Beach... not all of them make it.

programme.title: World War Two: Total War: A Terrible Precedent
programme.desc: Each episode looks at a different aspect, starting with an exploration of the portents of total war to come and moving through to preparations for war, followed by invasion, occupation and resistance and how total war enabled the Holocaust.

programme.title: World War Two: Total War: Arsenal of Democracy
programme.desc: Each episode looks at a different aspect, starting with an exploration of the portents of total war to come and moving through to preparations for war, followed by invasion, occupation and resistance and how total war enabled the Holocaust.

programme.title: World War Two: Total War: Unprecedented, Unmerciful and Unrelenting
programme.desc: Each episode looks at a different aspect, starting with an exploration of the portents of total war to come and moving through to preparations for war, followed by invasion, occupation and resistance and how total war enabled the Holocaust.

programme.title: World War Two: Total War: Fear of the Air
programme.desc: Each episode looks at a different aspect, starting with an exploration of the portents of total war to come and moving through to preparations for war, followed by invasion, occupation and resistance and how total war enabled the Holocaust.

programme.title: World War Two: Total War: Rejoice in Life
programme.desc: Each episode looks at a different aspect, starting with an exploration of the portents of total war to come and moving through to preparations for war, followed by invasion, occupation and resistance and how total war enabled the Holocaust.

programme.title: Hitler's Secret Sex Life: X-Rated
programme.desc: Adolf Hitler had a depraved sex life that he tried to keep hidden from the German public. He was said to be a chronic masturbator, a voyeur and that he engaged in sado-masochistic sex with women.

programme.title: Hitler's Secret Sex Life: Body Image
programme.desc: Hitler wanted the world to believe he possessed super-human qualities but in private he was a wreck. This episode reveals the archives that confirm Hitler’s genital deformity, the alarming truth about his heavy drug addiction and the Parkinson’s.

programme.title: Hitler's Secret Sex Life: Family Matters
programme.desc: Adolf Hitler's father was a violent, abusive man. His mother doted on her young son. This episode delves deep into the psychology of Hitler as the narcissistic child who grew into a malignant psychopath full of rage and deep hatred.

programme.title: Hitler's Secret Sex Life: Suicidal Maidens
programme.desc: Using extensive archival research, this program explores the squalid secrets he lied and killed to protect

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: From The "Protection Squadron" To The SS State.
programme.desc: From the Protection Squadron to the SS State: Trace the rise to power of the SS as we examine several perpetrators. Who was recruited? And why was the SS attractive to men?
programme.sub-title: From The "Protection Squadron" To The SS State.

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: Heinrich Himmler
programme.desc: Heinrich Himmler: An agriculturalist by trade, he went on to lead the SS and tried to escape responsibility at the end of the war. Who was Heinrich Himmler?

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: The Executioner: Reinhard Heydrich
programme.desc: The Executioner: Reinhard Heydrich: More than any other Nazi leader, Heydrich was an orchestrator of mass murder, and was terrifyingly clinical in approach.

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: The Waffen-SS
programme.desc: The Waffen-SS: Masqueraded as military excellence, the reality was very different. Recruits were poorly trained and remorse was nonexistent, as SS troops killed mercilessly.

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: The SS Death Head's Unit
programme.desc: The SS Death Head's Unit: Tasked with guarding concentration camps, this unit's actions knew no bounds, and, despite their heinous acts, still attended social gatherings.

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: Unrepentant: The SS And Its Myth After 1945
programme.desc: Unrepentant: The SS and Its Myth After 1945: Drawing a line to the present, the atrocities of the SS are beyond all doubt, yet, there is a cult surrounding 'old comrades' today.
programme.sub-title: Unrepentant: The SS And Its Myth After 1945

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: The Seeds of Violence 1918-1922
programme.desc: The Seeds of Violence 1918-1922: In the wake of the First World War, Adolf Hitler identifies Benito Mussolini as his model and has one ultimate goal: to gain power in Germany.

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: Deceit and Delusion 1923-1928
programme.desc: Deceit and Delusion 1923-1928: Hitler appears to be eliminated after his failed putsch in 1923. Discover how the Nazi movement used democracy's tolerance in Germany to come back.

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: Democracy without Democrats 1929-1933
programme.desc: Democracy Without Democrats 1929-1933: A protest turns into a racist and anti-Jewish movement during the 1920s and the NSDAP use emotions to gain the loyalty of the people.

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: The Racial State 1933-1934
programme.desc: The Racial State 1933-1934: President Hindenburg suspends freedom of speech and Hitler comes to power in 1933. The first concentration camps for political opponents are set up.

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: Hidden in Plain Sight 1935-1938
programme.desc: Hidden In Plain Sight 1935-1938: In 1934, Hitler's government is firmly in the saddle. Most Germans support Hitler's anti-Jewish policy and the regime's terror soon escalates.

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: Up in Flames 1936-1940
programme.desc: Up in Flames 1936-1940: At the end of 1939, the German Army invades Poland. Examine how Hitler succeeded in pushing through his rearmament and war plans relatively unhindered.

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: The Gates of Hell 1941-1942
programme.desc: The Gates of Hell 1941-1942: In the shadow of the war, the Nazi regime gradually advances its "final solution to the Jewish problem", culminating in the Holocaust.

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: Genocide 1942-1944
programme.desc: Genocide 1942 - 1944: Along with Treblinka and Majdanek, Sobibor was one of the camps used in Operation Reinhard, in which the Nazis murdered almost two million people.

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: Armageddon 1943-1945
programme.desc: Armageddon 1943-1945: The defeat at Stalingrad in 1943 was the turning point of the war and convinced the Nazi leadership to intensify their terror and propaganda campaigns.

programme.title: Giant Constructions: Railway Bridges

programme.title: The Island with Bear Grylls

programme.title: The Island with Bear Grylls

programme.title: The Island with Bear Grylls

programme.title: The Island with Bear Grylls

programme.title: The Island with Bear Grylls

programme.title: Atonement
programme.desc: This film shows efforts being made by wildlife specialists to preserve and nurture the creatures that do remain in our wilderness areas. Scenes rarely photographed make this a spellbinding film throughout.

programme.title: Writer In The Nuclear Age A Conversation With Margaret Laurence
programme.desc: Margaret Laurence tackles peace-related issues in this short film: writer's social responsibility, language's impact, nuclear threat, and more. Ideal for sparking discussions across various subjects.

programme.title: The Fate Of America
programme.desc: On Sept 13, 1759, the Battle of the Plains of Abraham sealed America's fate in 20 mins. 'The Fate of America' explores this myth, leaving French Canadians pondering defeat. Filmmaker Jacques Godbout's take unites Montcalm and Wolfe's descendants.

programme.title: Illuminated Lives A Brief History Of Womens Work In The Middle Ages
programme.desc: The popular image of the Middle Ages comes from fairy tales and romances. This animated short challenges some enduring myths about medieval women and shows what their lives were really like.

programme.title: Strings
programme.desc: Strings: a haunting film of intimate strangers linked by shared spaces. Comfortable connections fracture when a problem arises. Created with glass painting and stop-motion, it's visually stunning.

programme.title: Beyond Paper
programme.desc: In the era of the digital revolution, the transmission of knowledge is going through a profound upheaval as humanity’s archives migrate from paper to the cloud. How can we grasp the impact of the ongoing abandonment of books on thought and learning?

programme.title: The Tree That Remembers
programme.desc: In 1992, an Iranian student took his life in Ontario, haunted despite refuge in Canada. Masoud Raouf's 'The Tree that Remembers' unites former political prisoners, honoring the dead and celebrating resilience with testimony, footage, and art.

programme.title: Last Chance
programme.desc: Last Chance by Paul Émile d’Entremont travels the world to tell the stories of five asylum seekers who flee their native countries to escape homophobic violence. Here in Canada, they face hurdles integrating into society and fear deportation.

programme.title: Abortion Stories From North And South
programme.desc: This film provides a historical overview of how church, state and the medical establishment have determined policies concerning abortion.

programme.title: Its Just Better
programme.desc: At the farmhouse on Cape Breton Island where Shawn Peter Dwyer, age ten, lives with his mother and nine brothers and sisters, a team effort keeps the family functioning.

programme.title: Firewords Louky Bersianik Jovette Marchessault Nicole Brossa
programme.desc: Firewords offers an intimate glimpse of three respected, controversial Québec writers.Louky Bersianik, Jovette Marchessault and Nicole Brossard have contributed greatly to the creation of a distinctive women's literature.

programme.title: Proudest Girl In The World, The
programme.desc: A musical recruiting film for the Canadian Women's Army Corp.

programme.title: This Borrowed Land
programme.desc: This Borrowed Land" highlights women farmers in BC's Peace River Valley, protesting hydro dam construction threatening their farmland. They question land use, food production, and their children's future in a film on agriculture, ecology, and resilience.

programme.title: Ill Find A Way
programme.desc: When nine-year-old Nadia is allowed to attend a regular school, she knows the kids will tease her but she'll "find a way to deal with it." Nadia has spina bifida, a congenital condition that has caused a lack of sensation from the knees down.

programme.title: George And Rosemary
programme.desc: George and Rosemary is an animated romantic comedy about two golden agers who prove that passion is not exclusively for the young.

programme.title: Minoru Memory Of Exile
programme.desc: The bombing of the American naval base at Pearl Harbor, by a nation he knew only by name, thrust nine-year-old Minoru Fukushima into a world of racism so malevolent he would be forced to leave Canada, the land of his birth.

programme.title: Adams World
programme.desc: Adam's World present a short lecture by Elizabeth Dodson Gray, a feminist theologian, environmentalist, and futurist. She speaks to us about the severity of our global environmental crisis, and analyzes the root cause of this crisis.

programme.title: Voices Across The Water
programme.desc: ‘Voices Across the Water’ follows two master boat builders as they practise their art and find a way back to balance and healing.

programme.title: Doctor Lawyer Indian Chief
programme.desc: A tribute to Indigenous women everywhere, this short documentary focuses on 5 women from across Canada. They talk about the importance of Indigenous culture in helping them to develop a sense of self and seeing through rough times.

programme.title: Undertaker For Life!
programme.desc: Undertakers are anything but gloomy; they’re funny, generous and dedicated. We would gladly go on vacation with them, but sadly, they never have any dead time.

programme.title: Flamenco At 515
programme.desc: This Oscar-winning film is a visual and emotional thriller. It is an impressionistic record of a flamenco dance class given to senior students at the National Ballet School of Canada by two great teachers from Spain, Susana and Antonio Robledo.

programme.desc: GoldStar TV feiert die Showlegende Freddy Quinn mit seinem legendären Abschieds-Konzert aus dem Wiener Konzerthaus. Er begeisterte mit all seinen Evergreens wie "Heimatlos", "La Paloma" und "Junge, komm bald wieder".

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute: zu Gast am Achensee
programme.desc: Rund um den romantischen Tiroler Achensee trifft Dagmar Obernosterer die Stars der Volksmusik. Henry Arland, Marc Pircher, Petra Frey, die Grubertaler, die Zillertaler Haderlumpen, u.v.a. präsentieren ihre Hits.

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute: zu Gast in Bad Kleinkirchheim
programme.desc: Dagmar Obernosterer präsentiert Bad Kleinkirchheim und die Region Nockberge in Kärnten. Sie besucht die Nockalmstrasse mit dem Naturbegegnungspark Silva Magica, den Millstätter See und die Kaiserburg, Hausberg von Ski-Olympiasieger Franz Klammer.

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute: zu Gast im Winterwunderland Kärnten
programme.desc: Traumhafte Winterlandschaften und Skiregionen - Dagmar Obernosterer begrüßt das Nockalm Quintett, Marc Pircher, die jungen Zillertaler, Bartl Gensbichler mit seiner Skilehrermusi, die Original Fidelen Mölltaler und auch Olympiasieger Franz Klammer.

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute: zu Gast in der Steiermark
programme.desc: Dagmar Obernosterer präsentiert diesmal in der Steiermark große Stars der volkstümlichen Schlagermusik: Die Mooskirchner, Die Schäfer, Die Aufgeiger, Reiner Kirsten, Die Jauntaler, Eva-Maria, Die Krieglacher und Die Neffen.

programme.title: Stars auf hoher See: Von der Adria bis zum Bosporus Teil 2
programme.desc: Auch in Teil 2 der "Schlager-Kreuzfahrt" entführen die Moderatoren Frederic Meisner und Sonja Weissensteiner an die herrlichsten Orte zwischen der Adria und dem Bosporus. Mit an Bord sind unter anderem Bernhard Brink, Helene Fischer und Mary Roos.
programme.sub-title: Von der Adria bis zum Bosporus Teil 2

programme.title: Goldies: Folge 2
programme.desc: Er schenkte mir den Eiffelturm / Verlieben, verloren, vergessen, verzeihn / Theater / Moskau / Let your love flow / Rocky / Mississippi

programme.title: Schlagergala 2007: Teil 1
programme.desc: Uwe Hübner präsentiert die A.D.S.-Schlager-Gala aus Dorf Münsterland. Gekonnt führt er durch das Programm und selbstverständlich kommt auch die Musik nicht zu kurz. Hochkaräter wie Costa Cordalis, Nik P. mit Claudia Jung, Heino u.v.a. sind dabei.

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute: zu Gast im Defereggental / Antholzertal
programme.desc: Die Stars der Volksmusik begleiten Dagmar Obernosterer vom Defereggental in Osttirol in das Antholzertal nach Südtirol. Gottfried Würcher, die jungen Zillertaler, Sarah-Stephanie, die Alpenrebellen u.v.a. sind dabei, wenn die Apres-Ski-Party beginnt.

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute: Rund um die Petzen Winterlust in der Region Klopeinersee /Südkärnten
programme.desc: Eine herrliche Bergkulisse und traumhafter Pistenspaß - die Grubertaler und Marc Pircher bringen eine ordentliche Portion Hüttenzauber in Ihr Wohnzimmer. Hochkarätige Interpreten wie Mara Kayser, Oswald Sattler & Doris Russo sind ebenfalls mit dabei..
programme.sub-title: Rund um die Petzen Winterlust in der Region Klopeinersee /Südkärnten

programme.title: Freddy Quinn LIVE - Lieder, die das Leben schrieb: Teil 1
programme.desc: Er reiste um die Welt, begeisterte ein Millionenpublikum und schaffte es zehn Mal auf Platz 1 der deutschen Charts. Freddy Quinn ist einer der letzten großen Entertainer Deutschlands. 2002 gab der Österreicher ein bewegendes Abschieds-Konzert in Wien.

programme.title: Peter Kraus - Ganz nah
programme.desc: Peter Kraus ist die deutsche Rock'n'Roll-Legende! Wie er privat denkt und fühlt, das zeigt sein Sohn Mike in einem außergewöhnlichen Portrait. Er begleitet seinen Vater auf Tournee und ermöglicht einzigartige Einblicke hinter die Kulissen.

programme.title: Goldies: Folge 1
programme.desc: Auf dem Mond da blühen keine Rosen / Cora komm nach Haus / Marleen / Ganz in Weiß / Du fängst den Wind niemals ein / Es fährt ein Zug nach Nirgendwo / Santa Maria

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute: zu Gast im Villnösser Tal in Südtirol
programme.desc: Dagmar Obernosterer präsentiert wieder die Stars der volkstümlichen Schlagermusik - diesmal vor der malerischen Kulisse des Villnösser Tals in Südtirol. Mit dabei sind unter anderem Oswald Sattler, die Zellberg Buam und Anneliese Breitenberger.
programme.sub-title: zu Gast im Villnösser Tal in Südtirol

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute: zu Gast in Kärnten
programme.desc: Dagmar Obernosterer stellt uns ihre Heimat Kärnten vor. Mit dabei sind u.a. die Schäfer, die Alpenrebellen, die Grubertaler, die Zellberg Buam, die Jungen Original Oberkrainer und der Sieger der Vorentscheidung zum Grand Prix der Volksmusik - Udo Wenders.

programme.title: Ein Festival der Liebe: Teil 2
programme.desc: Zu Tausenden strömten gut gelaunte Schlagerfans 2010 in den Dortmunder Revierpark Wischlingen, um ihre Lieblingsstars hautnah zu erleben. Nicole, Chris Roberts, Guildo Horn u.v.a. machten dieses Open Air Konzert zu einem echten "Festival der Liebe".

programme.title: Tempo de Natal
programme.desc: Dois irmãos distantes tentam se reconectar no Natal, mas há algo que um deles não consegue superar: o outro pensa que é um viajante do tempo.

programme.title: Véspera de Natal
programme.desc: É véspera de Natal e um apagão vai obrigar alguns nova-iorquinos ocupados a ficarem presos dentro de elevadores enquanto esperam por ajuda. Essa longa noite juntos irá mudar suas vidas para sempre.

programme.title: Um Homem de Família
programme.desc: Jack Campbell é um solteiro convicto que há 13 anos desistiu de um grande amor para se tornar um empresário bem sucedido. Até que na véspera do Natal ele passa por uma experiência traumática e, ao acordar, vê-se numa nova vida.

programme.title: O Projeto de Natal
programme.desc: Quatro irmãos unem forças para se vingar dos Hagbarts, os valentões mais malvados de sua escola.

programme.title: O Natal Prometido
programme.desc: Quando uma queda de energia causa pânico em uma loja, eles são separados um do outro. Cada um sentiu uma conexão com o outro, mas eles não têm como se reconectar. Com a aproximação do Natal, nem Kim nem Theo podem esquecer o outro.

programme.title: Lucia e o Cristal Mágico
programme.desc: Lucia é a primeira menina da Escola Internacional de Natal. Quando seu melhor amigo, Oscar, é acusado de roubar o cristal mágico do Rei Inverno, que alimenta a máquina atual, Lucia se propõe a provar a inocência dele.

programme.title: Festividades do Chocolate Quente
programme.desc: Colette dirige uma cafetaria conhecida pelo seu chocolate quente secreto e famoso. Marcus, um novo dono de sobremesa, começa a atrair os clientes da Colette, ela está determinada a expô-lo.

programme.title: Um Anjo em Minha Vida
programme.desc: Uma jovem adolescente rica e mimada está prestes a descobrir que o verdadeiro valor não está nas etiquetas de preços e "coisas", mas nos atos gentis de ajudar os outros, tudo com a mão amiga de um anjo da guarda.

programme.title: Desejo de Natal
programme.desc: Sem dinheiro e abandonada pelo marido com três filhos, Martha não está tendo o melhor fim de ano da sua vida. Mas ela muda de cidade e redescobre a esperança quando encontra um emprego e uma rede de apoio em uma pacata lanchonete de interior.

programme.title: Natal Feliz
programme.desc: Após a morte de seu pai, um menino cria um vínculo especial com o cachorro de um vizinho e aprende a ser um homem ajudando seus avós durante uma tempestade de inverno.

programme.title: Fabric of Christmas, The
programme.desc: Liam, un bombero, y Amy, una profesora de acolchado, se unen para hacer una colcha navideña para la boda de la hermana de Liam, pero su romance se ve amenazado por el plan de Liam de viajar a Sudamérica.

programme.title: Una Navidad Casi Perfecta
programme.desc: Tras perder su trabajo y novio, una aspirante a novelista se muda a Sunshine Coast y descubre las complejidades del amor.

programme.title: A Vineyard Christmas
programme.desc: Heather, presentadora del popular programa de Tannin TV, está decidida a crear el episodio navideño perfecto presentando una bodega única de su ciudad natal en Vermont, pero choca con el dueño de la bodega.

programme.title: Una aldea navideña
programme.desc: Para salvar su reputación, Piper Jensen, una genio en relaciones públicas y dueña de su propia agencia de relaciones públicas, acepta trabajar para el dueño de un Pueblo de Santa en dificultades, ahí descubrirá el amor y cuán mágica es la navidad.

programme.title: Holiday Joy
programme.desc: Una tímida estudiante de secundaria pide un deseo de Navidad, el tener una familia perfecta, pero cuando su deseo se hace realidad, no es tan perfecto como ella pensó que sería.

programme.title: A Vineyard Christmas

programme.title: Parejas de navidad
programme.desc: Las mejores amigas Sarah, Cat y Riley se reúnen para disfrutar de la magia navideña con sus familias. Con cada amigo en una encrucijada diferente, todos tendrán que unirse para redescubrir la magia navideña que sucede en la casa de Holly Lane.

programme.title: Otra vez Navidad
programme.desc: Un chico travieso se despierta cada mañana del día de Navidad con la ilusión de tener un regalo, pero nunca lo recibe. La única manera de romper esta maldición es darse cuenta de que es un egoísta y corregir su actitud.

programme.title: Juntos en navidad
programme.desc: Una mujer se enamora mientras alquila la casa de huéspedes de un papá joven en Navidad.

programme.title: 12 Días De Regalos
programme.desc: Baxter es fotógrafo y ha recibido un premio en metálico. Con él puede pagar la boda con su novia, pero a medida que va surtiendo de regalos a gente necesitada ese dinero merma, y su chica se enfada.

programme.desc: Liam, un bombero, y Amy, una profesora de acolchado, se unen para hacer una colcha navideña para la boda de la hermana de Liam, pero su romance se ve amenazado por el plan de Liam de viajar a Sudamérica.

programme.desc: Tras perder su trabajo y novio, una aspirante a novelista se muda a Sunshine Coast y descubre las complejidades del amor.

programme.title: A Vineyard Christmas
programme.desc: Heather, presentadora del popular programa de Tannin TV, está decidida a crear el episodio navideño perfecto presentando una bodega única de su ciudad natal en Vermont, pero choca con el dueño de la bodega.

programme.title: Una aldea navideña
programme.desc: Para salvar su reputación, Piper Jensen, una genio en relaciones públicas y dueña de su propia agencia de relaciones públicas, acepta trabajar para el dueño de un Pueblo de Santa en dificultades, ahí descubrirá el amor y cuán mágica es la navidad.

programme.title: Holiday Joy
programme.desc: Una tímida estudiante de secundaria pide un deseo de Navidad, el tener una familia perfecta, pero cuando su deseo se hace realidad, no es tan perfecto como ella pensó que sería.

programme.title: A Vineyard Christmas

programme.title: Parejas de navidad
programme.desc: Las mejores amigas Sarah, Cat y Riley se reúnen para disfrutar de la magia navideña con sus familias. Con cada amigo en una encrucijada diferente, todos tendrán que unirse para redescubrir la magia navideña que sucede en la casa de Holly Lane.

programme.title: Otra vez Navidad
programme.desc: Un chico travieso se despierta cada mañana del día de Navidad con la ilusión de tener un regalo, pero nunca lo recibe. La única manera de romper esta maldición es darse cuenta de que es un egoísta y corregir su actitud.

programme.title: Juntos en navidad
programme.desc: Una mujer se enamora mientras alquila la casa de huéspedes de un papá joven en Navidad.

programme.title: 12 Días De Regalos

programme.title: A Vineyard Christmas
programme.desc: Heather, presentadora del popular programa de Tannin TV, está decidida a crear el episodio navideño perfecto presentando una bodega única de su ciudad natal en Vermont, pero choca con el dueño de la bodega.

programme.title: Una aldea navideña
programme.desc: Para salvar su reputación, Piper Jensen, una genio en relaciones públicas y dueña de su propia agencia de relaciones públicas, acepta trabajar para el dueño de un Pueblo de Santa en dificultades, ahí descubrirá el amor y cuán mágica es la navidad.

programme.title: Holiday Joy
programme.desc: Una tímida estudiante de secundaria pide un deseo de Navidad, el tener una familia perfecta, pero cuando su deseo se hace realidad, no es tan perfecto como ella pensó que sería.

programme.title: A Vineyard Christmas

programme.title: Parejas de navidad
programme.desc: Las mejores amigas Sarah, Cat y Riley se reúnen para disfrutar de la magia navideña con sus familias. Con cada amigo en una encrucijada diferente, todos tendrán que unirse para redescubrir la magia navideña que sucede en la casa de Holly Lane.

programme.title: Otra vez Navidad
programme.desc: Un chico travieso se despierta cada mañana del día de Navidad con la ilusión de tener un regalo, pero nunca lo recibe. La única manera de romper esta maldición es darse cuenta de que es un egoísta y corregir su actitud.

programme.title: Juntos en navidad
programme.desc: Una mujer se enamora mientras alquila la casa de huéspedes de un papá joven en Navidad.

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute zu Gast im Defereggental
programme.desc: Dagmar Obernosterer präsentiert in dieser Folge der beliebten Fernsehsendung Lieder, Land und Leute das Defereggental in Osttirol. Wenn Landschaften Lieder schreiben könnten, dann würde die naturbelassene, herrliche Bergkulisse des Defereggentals wohl auch jeden musikalischen Wettbewerb gewinnen. In einem der unberührtesten Hochgebirgstälern der Alpen mit saftigen Almwiesen, Bergseen, seltenen Pflanzen und Tieren präsentieren die bekanntesten Interpreten der volkstümlichen Schlagermusik ihre Hits.

programme.title: Schlagerolympiade
programme.desc: GoldStar TV präsentiert die Schlagerolympiade aus der Münchner Olympiahalle. Freuen Sie sich auf Auftritte von Patrick Lindner, Tony Christie, Rosanna Rocci und den Olsen Brothers.

programme.title: Bei Hübner
programme.desc: Geboren wurde Ireen Sheer in England am 25. Februar 1949. Bevor sie sich ganz auf ihre Musik konzentrierte, machte sie zunächst eine Banklehre. In den 70er-Jahren hatte sie in Deutschland ihren großen Durchbruch und zählt bis heute zu den erfolgreichsten Schlagersängerinnen des Landes. Dieser Talk-Klassiker ist ein faszinierendes Zeitdokument einer außergewöhnlich erfolgreichen Künstlerin, die Ende 2022 ihr Karriereende bekanntgab.

programme.title: Herzgschichtn
programme.desc: Er ist in Bayern dahoam und in der Welt zu Hause, doch sein Herz wird immer für seine bayerische Heimat schlagen. Max Weidner, der Sänger aus der Oberpfalz, der bunte Tattoos, seine Herkunft und die Liebe zum Schlager miteinander vereint, ist zu Gast in Kirchberg bei Kitzbühel. Im Gespräch mit Anja Viktoria Autenrieth macht er deutlich, dass es ihm im Leben nicht darum geht, reich, schön oder berühmt zu sein. Vielmehr geht es darum, sich selbst treu zu bleiben und sich dabei auch nicht immer allzu ernst zu nehmen.

programme.title: First Moments der Schlagerstars 2
programme.desc: Der herzliche Moderator Peter Grimberg geht den Geschichten, die das Leben schreibt, auf die Spur. In der Sendung ‚First Moments‘ reist er mit seinen prominenten Gästen in deren Vergangenheit und beleuchtet ihren ganz persönlichen Lebensweg.

programme.desc: Sein Hüftschwung ist so legendär wie der von Elvis. Und als Sänger, Gitarrist und Gelegenheitsschauspieler war Peter Kraus einer der ersten deutschsprachigen Künstler, die den Rock'n'Roll im Nachkriegsdeutschland salonfähig machten - mit Songs wie 'Susi Rock', 'Sugar Baby' oder 'Schwarze Rose Rosemarie'.

programme.desc: Der Mittlere Osten ist eines der heißesten, trockensten Gebiete der Erde, mit Jordanien in seinem Herzen. Das harte Leben der Tiere wird hier von der Sonne regiert. Jedes Jahr steigen die Temperaturen und die Wüste wächst.

programme.title: DIE HALBINSEL
programme.desc: Einer der symbolträchtigsten Lebensräume der iberischen Halbinsel ist der Mittelmeerwald, das Land des Iberischen Luchses, einer einzigartigen und faszinierenden Raubkatze mit einer Erfolgsgeschichte bei der Erhaltung der Tiere. Korkeichen und Steineichen sind die Herren dieser herrlichen Wälder. Und diese Wälder beherbergen eine einzigartige und endemische Fauna. Damit ist diese Region einer der wichtigsten Biodiversitäts-Hotspots der Erde.

programme.title: Wilde Überlebenskünstler
programme.desc: Sich um die eigenen Kinder zu kümmern ist der wunderbarste Job der Welt. Aber es ist auch der schwerste, anstrengendste, komplizierteste und manchmal wirklich aufreibendste. Ab und zu kann man fast nachvollziehen, dass manche Tiere sich gar nicht um ihren Nachwuchs kümmern.

programme.desc: Diese Serie feiert Lateinamerikas dramatischste Regionen, von den Hohen Anden zum dampfenden Amazonas, von den windigen Steppen Patagoniens zu den Sümpfen Venezuelas – atemberaubende Schönheit und eine aufregende, vielfältige Tierwelt.

programme.title: Der Whisky-Mythos von Islay
programme.desc: Die schottische Insel Islay ist Heimat von acht traditionellen Whisky-Brennereien, die unter Kennern einen ausgezeichneten Ruf genießen. Das Wasser, der Torf und das Jod des Meeres sind die besonderen Elemente des Whiskys, der die Insel berühmt gemacht hat. Doch nicht nur das: Die Herstellung des berühmten Getränks sorgt für Arbeitsplätze auf Islay, ist Stolz und zugleich Lebensgrundlage ihrer charismatischen Bewohner. Planet Weltweit hat die Insel besucht und erlebt, wie das schottische Nationalgetränk Leben und Arbeit der Menschen auf Islay bestimmt.

programme.title: Marokkos weißes Gold
programme.desc: Die Arganie, ein dornenbewehrter Baum, wächst nur im Südwesten Marokkos. Seine Früchte liefern das begehrte Arganöl, welches von den Frauen der Region seit Jahrhunderten in mühevoller Handarbeit produziert wird. Inzwischen kommen auch Europäer auf den Geschmack dieser einzigartigen Kostbarkeit. Und nicht nur das: Neben seinen kulinarischen Qualitäten lässt sich das Öl ebenso gut als Kosmetikprodukt und Heilmittel vermarkten. Planet Weltweit hat den Frauen Marokkos bei der aufwändigen Ölherstellung über die Schulter geschaut und beobachtet, wie sie sie versuchen, ihr traditionelles Kleinod für den internationalen Wettbewerb vorzubereiten.Sechs Uhr morgens in einem kleinen Dorf im Südwesten Marokkos. Die Männer sind bereits zur Arbeit aufgebrochen. Auch Arbia el Kasri verlässt das Haus, um ihrem Beruf nachzugehen. Vor fünf Jahren noch war es für eine Frau unvorstellbar außerhalb des Hauses Arbeit zu finden. In dieser Region Marokkos verlassen die Bäuerinnen eigentlich nie ihre Douar, ihre kleinen Dörfer. Doch nun sind es einige Hunderte, die sich wie Arbia täglich in kleinen Kooperativen einfinden, welche die Frauen selbst gegründet haben. Hier produzieren sie Arganöl - eine Kunst, die Marokkanerinnen bereits seit Jahrhunderten beherrschen. Das Öl ist überaus nährstoffre ...

programme.title: Der Weinpriester von Bali
programme.desc: Bali - Tropenparadies und Insel der Götter. Dem 42-jährigen Hindu Rai Budarsa gelang es als Erstem, Wein auf Bali zu kultivieren. Dreimal im Jahr kann auf der tropischen Insel geerntet werden. Für den Unternehmer ein Segen - doch für den gläubigen Hindu in Anbetracht der vielen religiösen Feste und Zeremonien eine Herausforderung. Ob Rai Budarsa der Balanceakt zwischen dem harten Alltag eines Unternehmers und seinen religiösen Verpflichtungen gelingt, davon erzählt diese Episode von Planet Weltweit.Bereits seit einer Stunde wartet die Prozession für die Leichenbestattung auf der Straße. Rai Budarsa streift eilig sein Poloshirt und die Bermudas ab, denn als höchster Vertreter einer Priesterkaste muss er jede Zeremonie in seiner Gemeinde leiten. Als sein Blackberry klingelt, schafft er es gerade noch den Knoten seines schwarzen Sarongs festzuziehen, bevor er den Anruf entgegennimmt. Es ist sein Kellermeister, der Australier Don Buchanan: Ihm fehlen Flaschen für die Abfüllung des Pino de Bali, dem Spitzenprodukt seines Unternehmens Hatten Wines. Der Container mit den Flaschen hängt irgendwo fest - ausgerechnet jetzt, wo während der religiösen Feiertage auf Bali die Restaurants und Hotels mit dem regionalen Wein beliefert werden müssen. Im Laufschritt verspricht Rai Budar ...

programme.title: Die Köchin von Bahia
programme.desc: Die afro-brasilianische Kultur ist nirgendwo so lebendig wie in Salvador de Bahia und in der Religion Candombl?. Die Köchin Elaine Cruz lebt und kocht nach den Regeln dieser Religion und zaubert einzigartige Spezialitäten, die Götter und Menschen gleichermaßen munden. Planet Weltweit hat Elaine beim Kochen für ein großes Fest einer Candombl?-Gemeinde über die Schulter geschaut.

programme.title: Brasilien
programme.desc: Die Einwohner der Amazonas-Insel Marajo nutzen außergewöhnliche Reittiere, um die sumpfigen Mangrovenwälder ihrer Heimat zu durchdringen: asiatische Wasserbüffel. Sie dienen als Nutz-, Haus- und Arbeitstiere, selbst die Polizei greift auf sie zurück: als einzige berittene Büffelstaffel der Welt. Planet Weltweit hat die ungewöhnliche Truppe bei der Arbeit mit den wuchtigen Reittieren begleitet.

programme.title: Im Land der schwarzen Witwen
programme.desc: Die Schwarze Witwe hat einen schlechten Ruf, kein Wunder, denn das Gift dieser Spinnenart ist 15-mal stärker als das der Klapperschlange. Doch kann diese Substanz, als Medizin eingesetzt, auch Leben retten. Um an das Gift zu gelangen, geht das Ehepaar Kristensen regelmäßig in der Wüste von Arizona auf Spinnenjagd. Wir begleiten die Fangaktionen und die Zucht der hochgiftigen Tiere.

programme.title: Tasmanien
programme.desc: Tasmanien ist ein einzigartiges Naturparadies: Wilde Strände, dichter Regenwald, zerklüftete Bergketten und alpine Moorlandschaften vereinen sich auf engstem Raum. Auf der Insel leben Wombats, Schnabeligel und Tasmanische Teufel. Die Rangerin Lalani Hyatt patrouilliert täglich durch das Arthur-Pieman-Schutzgebiet, bekämpft Waldbrände, stellt Umweltsünder oder rettet verwaiste Jungtiere.

programme.title: Indien Summer am Polarkreis
programme.desc: Der Herrgott, so ein Sprichwort in der Region, hat ihn nach der Schöpfung einfach vergessen: den Wald im Muddus Nationalpark in Schweden. Ein Urwald - die eine Hälfte voller Bäume, die andere voller Sümpfe und Seen, in dem die älteste Kiefer Schwedens steht. Wenn der Herbst die Bäume und Moose in goldgelbe und tiefrote Farbe taucht, spricht man auch hier im hohen Norden vom Indian Summer.

programme.title: Das Perlenimperium von Palawan
programme.desc: Sie schimmert warm und golden, die Oberfläche ist makellos: So sieht die perfekte Perle der goldlippigen Auster Pinctada Maxima aus. Ihr Wert - mehrere Tausend Euro. In freier Natur findet nur sich in einer von 20.000 Austern eine solche Kostbarkeit. Das Unternehmen Jewelmer hat deshalb vor Jahren angefangen, in den Gewässern des philippinischen Archipels Palawan, diese Austern zu züchten. Bis heute beträgt ihre Ausbeute mehrere Millionen Euro pro Jahr. Diesen Erfolg hat das Unternehmen einer akribischen Forschung und einer rigiden Personalpolitik zu verdanken. Planet hat den Archipel besucht und beobachtet, wie lange es dauert, der Natur diese seltenen Kostbarkeiten abzuringen.
